$interpreted:
Yan-Bo: So far from home into my deeds to pry, The scope and tenure of thy jealousy,
We few, we happy few, we band of brothers...
Pang: So it is the time... this festival again.
Yan-Bo: Yes, time of this festival it is.
Puggi: Ooh~ hi there Hearty Hestia~~
Puggi: Pang, what kind of fun stories are you guys rambling about!
Puggi: Don't you know that the story can't progress without the main character? Starting without me... tch tch, where's your common sense!
Pang: Idiot, you're only a mascot.
Puggi: Puuhahaha, you're always so funny when you talk!
Yan-Bo: Talking about a traditional festival of Eastern Alliance, we were. At time of this year, row dragon boats, eat zongzi, we will.
Hestia: Zongzi? What is that?
Yan-Bo: Cuisine with sticky rice, chestnut, mushrooms, and other fillings wrap with bamboo leaves into triangular shape, zongzi is.

Puggi: Bamboo leaves, sticky rice, chestnut, mushrooms.
Wrap into a triangular shape.
Hestia: Sounds very tasty.
Puggi: Eww, everything mush together into a hodgepodge of crap; sounds super gross.
Pang: You're the one that's a hodgepodge of crap.
Puggi: Hey! No Violence!

Pang: Zongzi is a traditional delicacy with great history. 
I will not allow you to insult it.
Hestia: Is it really that delicious?

Yan-Bo: Once tasted, fall in love with it, you will. 
I guarantee.
Pang: I truly miss that hometown flavor.
Yan-Bo: Ingredients, don't have, unfortunately. If available, more than willing to make some for everyone, I am.
Puggi: What's with all the fuss! Tasty this, delicious that; does it taste as good as me?
Puggi: I know! How about I made some zongzi myself!

Puggi: Pang's gonna cry rivers once he tastes them. 
Then he'll gladly accept his place as my loyal minion!
Puggi: No ingredients, pffft. Lookie here, ingredients everywhere, available in abundant numbers!
Puggi: My~ I'm such a genius that I scare myself sometimes.
Puggi: I choose you, to be filling for the zongzi!
Puggi: I recall Yan-Bo mentioning chestnuts as one of the ingredients, right?
